<LocalizedProperties><Language>en</Language><Title>Security Update for Windows 2000 (KB921503)</Title><Description>A security issue has been identified that could allow an attacker to remotely compromise your Windows-based system using Object Linking and Embedding (OLE) Automation and gain control over it. You can help protect your computer by installing this update from Microsoft. After you install this item, you may have to restart your computer.</Description><UninstallNotes>This software update can be removed via Add/Remove Programs in Control Panel.</UninstallNotes><MoreInfoUrl>http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?linkid=70249</MoreInfoUrl><SupportUrl>http://support.microsoft.com</SupportUrl></LocalizedProperties>